• Connections by the Portmaster itself are always allowed.
  • Communications are re-evaluated on the next new connection when a Profile has changed, Links are never re-evaluated.
  • Links may be inspected by additional modules, which can then deny previously permitted Links, but not permit previously denied ones.
  • Technically, denied inbound packets are always dropped, denied outgoing packets are blocked with a TCP Reset or an ICMP port-unreachable error message.
